13.body: This is the implementation the Hitachi hd44780 LCD display.
13.title: LCD

15.body: This LCD controller works on I2C, in this case the driver was implemented to be used on the STM32 board. Now this LCD required the following config: 10 MHz clock speed
15.title: Overview

16.body:
You can copy the following code to quickly test the driver: void main(){ LCD_init(); int32_t temp; LCD_send_txt((uint8_t *)"Temperature"); while(1){ temp = MS5611_read_temp(); LCD_update_value(0,12,temp); // dynamically writes onto LCD }
}

3.body: This sensor works for either SPI or I2C, in this case the driver was implemented for SPI only, to be used on the STM32 board. Now this sensor required the following config: 20 MHz clock speed SPI mode 0
3.title: Overview

4.body:
You can copy the following code to quickly test the driver: void main(){ MS5611_init(); int32_t temp, pressure; while(1){ temp = MS5611_read_temp(); pressure = MS5611_read_pressure(); // show data to lcd, etc. }
}
